Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.25,0:01:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The world we live in is filled with myriad caves.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.52,0:01:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}People who vanish like smoke \Nare said to wander within...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.40,0:02:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}without their memories, without their souls...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.41,0:02:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? A letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.30,0:02:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not being delivered as they should these days...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.93,0:02:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's time for a replacement...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.89,0:02:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't addressed to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.90,0:02:54.65,Caligraph,,0,0,0,,{\pos(576,145)\frz53.481}Aya Tozawa
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.90,0:02:54.65,Caligraph,,0,0,0,,{\pos(924,205)\frz55.059}Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.09,0:02:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Aya?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.59,0:03:24.64,EP Title BG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2000,0)\p1\blur1}m 0 0 l 950 0 950 100 0 100
Dialogue: 1,0:03:18.59,0:03:24.64,EP Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2100,0)\be1}Pickers of Empty Cocoons
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.21,0:03:41.70,Caligraph,,0,0,0,,{\pos(712,412)\frz22.203}Aya Tozawa
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.21,0:03:41.70,Caligraph,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1208,237)}Village
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.21,0:03:41.70,Caligraph,,0,0,0,,{\pos(980,403)\frz22.541}Wishing for...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.21,0:03:41.70,Caligraph,,0,0,0,,{\pos(972,576)\frz23.184}...I'm Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.60,0:04:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Aya. How have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.90,0:04:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.38,0:04:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think, it's time to replace your {\i1}uro-san,{\i0} isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.58,0:04:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... Letters arrive torn-off...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.81,0:04:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes strange messages find their way in...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.03,0:04:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You're still doing this... using our old ones?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.41,0:04:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.27,0:04:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If your thoughts are always consumed \Nby someone who's gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.43,0:04:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the old man won't be able to rest in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.59,0:04:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ito-chan is still wandering somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.42,0:04:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't bring her back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.43,0:04:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let it go...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.02,0:04:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Call it fate and leave it at that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.22,0:05:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Aya-chan, this cocoon is empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.99,0:05:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right... that's unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.81,0:05:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Where could the pupa inside have gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.21,0:05:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Aya, Ito... Put that back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.26,0:05:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't pick empty cocoons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.82,0:05:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.05,0:05:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad things live inside in place of the pupa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.54,0:05:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the elder from the Head Family.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.71,0:06:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He comes a lot recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.87,0:06:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls, come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.25,0:06:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ito, Aya... Do you remember the Elder in the mountains?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.75,0:06:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder in the mountains?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.52,0:06:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You met him when you were two.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.89,0:06:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When children are born, it's our family custom to check them for "that".
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.07,0:06:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It would seem both of them can see the {\i1}uro-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.43,0:06:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,When they turn ten, I will come to get one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.89,0:07:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The Elder is an {\i1}uro{\i0} keeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.21,0:07:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a tradition passed down through our Tozawa family.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.54,0:07:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But for many years, no one with promise was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.99,0:07:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,One of you will have to go there,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.62,0:07:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but your parents say they cannot decide who...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.70,0:07:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one of you is the younger sister Aya?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.81,0:07:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,M... Me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.67,0:07:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder, I will go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.74,0:07:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.82,0:07:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.94,0:07:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No! If Ito-chan goes, I'm going, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.66,0:07:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Aya...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.04,0:07:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.47,0:07:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be difficult for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.95,0:08:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but it may be the best for your daughters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.53,0:08:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The Elder probably doesn't have much longer to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.06,0:08:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Living alone deep in the mountains would be miserable...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.41,0:08:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But being together will probably ease their loneliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.49,0:08:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not as though you'll never see them again...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.91,0:09:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave the door slightly open.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.64,0:09:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If there are {\i1}uro-san{\i0} around, we'll be swallowed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.87,0:09:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit down now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.12,0:09:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I've waited for a long time for this day to come,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.90,0:09:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but I never expected two at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.79,0:09:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you lived hereby yourself all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.15,0:09:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Ever since the elderly woman who preceded me passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.93,0:09:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,About the only people I spoke with are the mushi-shi who occasionally visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.93,0:09:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Their stories were all I had to look forward to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.90,0:09:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.47,0:09:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd tell them to you...\Nso I wrote many of them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.58,0:10:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, come on in now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.96,0:10:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This cocoon is empty, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.00,0:10:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a lot more here than \Nin the mountains around our village.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.21,0:10:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls, you know what double cocoons are, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.99,0:10:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.74,0:10:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Big cocoons formed by two pupae together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.52,0:10:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. I want you to find empty ones of that type.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.88,0:10:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do my work without them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.01,0:10:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.54,0:11:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally, cocoons consist of a single thread,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.09,0:11:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but double cocoons are made by two pupae, so they consist of two threads.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.47,0:11:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I unwind them and remake them into two cocoons,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.61,0:11:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but since that makes their "home" thinner overall,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.11,0:11:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the {\i1}uro-san{\i0} become confused and come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.42,0:11:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Aya, use that there to scoop it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.59,0:11:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done. Now place it in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.61,0:11:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's sealed in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.44,0:11:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The {\i1}uro-san{\i0} will only be able to go back and forth between these two cocoons for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.50,0:11:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Letter for you, Old Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.40,0:12:01.86,Caligraph,,0,0,0,,{\an8\3c&HDFE7E9&\shad0\bord2.5\c&H484F4F&\3a&H00&}Son fallen ill, vomiting day and night, weakning day by day,\Ncannot even lift a spoon. Urgently requesting a Mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.86,0:12:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, let's see... who's turn was it next?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.34,0:12:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the letter say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.81,0:12:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not addressed to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.13,0:12:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's a request to send a mushi-shi,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.66,0:12:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes it's a personal letter \Nfrom a mushi-shi's friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.49,0:12:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's use this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.12,0:12:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Mushi-shi are always on the move,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.21,0:12:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so if I put the letter in cocoon 1 like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.19,0:12:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the {\i1}uro-san{\i0} will eventually deliver it to \Nthe mushi-shi who has cocoon 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.01,0:12:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,However, they have to be replaced after a few years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.36,0:12:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Uro-san{\i0} rapidly expend their uro-passageway after leaving their cocoons.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.56,0:12:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, it penetrates through to a closed room somewhere or to another uro-passageway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.33,0:12:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When that happens, letters don't reliably get delivered.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.31,0:13:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Uro-san{\i0} are so interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.33,0:13:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder, next time, I'd like to insert the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.91,0:13:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ito, Aya. You mustn't underestimate the {\i1}uro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.69,0:13:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Uro-san{\i0} are frightening mushi that go around opening up holes in our world...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.83,0:13:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The area around here is conducive to {\i1}uro-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.74,0:13:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so they infest whenever they find an enclosed space.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.28,0:13:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you mustn't close the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.83,0:13:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If you mistakenly close a door, you must not open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.15,0:13:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you open the door and {\i1}uro-san{\i0} are inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.30,0:13:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,along with the escaping {\i1}uro-san,{\i0} you will be swept into the uro-passageway...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.96,0:13:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because {\i1}uro-san{\i0} cannot survive \Nvery long outside of closed spaces.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.31,0:13:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens if you're sucked in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.94,0:14:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They say that you're condemned to wander inside the uro-passageway the rest of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.10,0:14:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you follow my instructions,\Nthere's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.33,0:14:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I've lived to a ripe old age without an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.22,0:14:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't close {\i1}doors;{\i0} don't open doors...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.96,0:14:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Aya-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.14,0:14:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you done with the laundry?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.98,0:14:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.32,0:14:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder says we can play until evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.03,0:14:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? I'll be right thereafter\N I put this away. Wait for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.39,0:14:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Aya-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.29,0:14:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Be mindful of the storehouse door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.09,0:14:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.37,0:14:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What a lovely day...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.79,0:15:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Ito-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.10,0:15:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ito-chan... have you fallen asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.74,0:15:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't lift it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.91,0:15:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ito-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.32,0:16:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It was because I lifted the sheet...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.23,0:16:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I didn't pin it down as I should have...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.13,0:16:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Aya, it wasn't your fault...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.11,0:16:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did Ito-chan go?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.51,0:16:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we bring her back?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.69,0:16:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid... there is no way, Aya...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.40,0:16:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I am absolutely... going to bring Ito-chan back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.70,0:16:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We were always together.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.93,0:16:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I never imagined life without Ito-chan at my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.08,0:16:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's been five years since that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.31,0:16:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like you're still not eating well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.66,0:17:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,At least try to think about yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.75,0:17:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, would you like to enter the uro-passageway?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.93,0:17:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go in with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.69,0:17:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see for yourself what\N the uro-passageway is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.65,0:17:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.22,0:17:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When uro infest a tree that lies along the vein of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.35,0:17:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it causes an allergic reaction and forms into a gall.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.04,0:17:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Grab on to the chain and follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.87,0:18:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This... is an uro-passageway?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.81,0:18:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just the very end of it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.14,0:18:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, we'll come to an uro-cavern.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.99,0:18:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Who put this chain here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.12,0:18:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Mushi-shi from long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.13,0:18:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an old pathway used by mushi-shi as a shortcut.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.22,0:18:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They say some stayed too long and lost their memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.43,0:18:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I rarely use it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.74,0:19:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? Don't you wanna go farther?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.81,0:19:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all these passageways,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.89,0:19:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,they say the end of this chain is\Nthe only one that leads outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.37,0:19:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All the others connect to enclosed spaces somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.34,0:19:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that you cannot open up from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.30,0:19:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There are an infinite number of\N uro-caverns like this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.69,0:19:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The chances that your sister passed through here are exceedingly slim.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.58,0:19:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll never find her, no matter what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.72,0:19:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Let her go, Aya.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.46,0:20:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Close that huge hole in your heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.47,0:20:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,before you become unable to come out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.75,0:20:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ito... chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.65,0:21:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A strange tale was recorded in a certain silk-producing village some years later...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.17,0:21:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"A girl emerged from a cocoon. She was about ten but could not speak.''
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.15,0:21:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,S-s-s-s-somebody!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.74,0:21:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody, come quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.67,0:21:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}''Later, with the aid of the letter she had, she was returned to her home village.''
